    <briefdescription>
<para>Header file for the <ref refid="classDigitalOutputGuard" kindref="compound">DigitalOutputGuard</ref> class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="classDigitalOutputGuard" kindref="compound">DigitalOutputGuard</ref> class ensures that a DigitalGpio instance is set to output mode and active state in its constructor, and inactive in its destructor (RAII pattern). This provides safe automatic management of GPIO output states with guaranteed cleanup even in exception scenarios, ensuring proper resource management and pin state control.</para>
